!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

wipe /waɪp/

(wiping,wiped,wipes) 

1. V-T If you wipe something, you rub its surface to remove dirt or liquid from it. 擦拭 

例： I'll just wipe the table. 我只擦擦桌子。 

例： When he had finished washing he began to wipe the basin clean. 他洗漱完后开始把水盆擦干净。 

2. N-COUNT Wipe is also a noun. 擦拭 

例： Tomorrow I'm going to give the toys a good wipe as some seem a bit greasy. 明天我会把那些玩具好好擦拭一番，因为有些看上去有点油腻了。 

3. V-T If you wipe dirt or liquid from something, you remove it by using a cloth or your hand. (用布或手) 擦去 

例： Gleb wiped the sweat from his face. 格莱布擦去了脸上的汗水。 

4. N-COUNT A wipe is a small moist cloth for cleaning things and is designed to be used only once. 一次性湿巾 

例： ...antiseptic wipes. …一次性杀菌湿巾。

